msgid "How it works"
msgstr "How it works"

msgid "how_it_works_body"
msgstr "Nexusys Junior is a family kiosk system. Each child gets their own profile. The kiosk (laptop) runs a locked Chromium browser that shows the child's kiosk page. Children earn stars ⭐ by completing tasks. Stars are the currency — they spend them to watch videos or buy rewards from the shop."

msgid "Tasks → Stars"
msgstr "Tasks → Stars"

msgid "Stars → Videos / Rewards"
msgstr "Stars → Videos / Rewards"

msgid "Parent controls everything"
msgstr "Parent controls everything"

msgid "children_step1"
msgstr "Go to Children → New child. Set name, avatar emoji, colour, and video cost (stars per video session)."

msgid "children_step2"
msgstr "The child's kiosk URL is /kiosk/<id>. You'll find it on the home page after clicking the child's avatar."

msgid "children_step3"
msgstr "In child detail you can manually add or subtract stars, send a kiosk message (popup on screen), and manage devices and schedules."

msgid "Tasks & Chores"
msgstr "Tasks & Chores"

msgid "Reward tasks"
msgstr "Reward tasks"

msgid "reward_tasks_body"
msgstr "Created in the Tasks section. Parent taps a task in child detail to award stars immediately. Good for one-off things like \"cleaned room\" or \"helped with dishes\"."

msgid "Daily chores"
msgstr "Daily chores"

msgid "daily_chores_body"
msgstr "Created in Children → Chores for a specific weekday. The child marks them done directly in the kiosk. Stars are awarded automatically. They reset every week."

msgid "shop_body"
msgstr "Add rewards in the Shop section (e.g. \"Extra screen time\", \"Ice cream\"). Set a star cost. The child buys a reward from the kiosk — their balance drops immediately and a notification appears. You fulfil the reward in real life."

msgid "videos_step1"
msgstr "Create categories first (e.g. \"Fairy tales\", \"Education\"). Each can have its own icon and colour."

msgid "videos_step2"
msgstr "Add videos by YouTube URL or ID, or import a whole playlist with one click. The system fetches titles automatically (requires YouTube API key in .env)."

msgid "videos_step3"
msgstr "Each video can have a custom price or override rules (e.g. fairy tales are free between 19:00–20:30). Leave blank to use the child's default video cost."

msgid "tiles_body"
msgstr "Tiles are shortcuts shown on the kiosk home screen. They can point to any URL (external website, internal game, etc). Built-in tiles (Videos, Letters, Numbers) are always shown. Custom tiles appear below them. You can set a bilingual name — the kiosk shows the correct one based on the active language."

msgid "Devices & NixOS kiosk"
msgstr "Devices & NixOS kiosk"

msgid "nixos_step1"
msgstr "In child detail, add a device with a unique key (e.g. child-laptop). This key identifies the laptop to the server."

msgid "nixos_step2"
msgstr "Click ↓ NixOS next to the device to download a pre-filled .nix config file. Copy it to /etc/nixos/configuration.nix on the laptop and place your Caddy CA certificate as /etc/nixos/caddy-ca.crt."

msgid "nixos_step3"
msgstr "Run nixos-rebuild switch. The laptop boots into a locked kiosk. The agent polls /api/device-policy?deviceId=… every 15 seconds and switches Chromium to the kiosk URL or a lock screen based on policy."

msgid "nixos_step4"
msgstr "Toggle Allowed / Blocked on the device to instantly lock or unlock the kiosk. A custom lock message is shown on screen."

msgid "Tip:"
msgstr "Tip:"

msgid "nixos_tip"
msgstr "Set NEXUSYS_PUBLIC_URL=https://your-server-domain in .env so the downloaded NixOS config contains the correct server address automatically."

msgid "Screen time schedules"
msgstr "Screen time schedules"

msgid "schedules_body"
msgstr "In child detail, add schedules to automatically lock the kiosk during certain times (e.g. school hours, bedtime). You can set a weekday or apply it every day. A custom message is shown when locked. The kiosk checks schedules client-side every minute."

msgid "stats_body"
msgstr "The Statistics page shows star balance trends, videos watched per child, most-used tiles, and task completion rate for the last 30 days. Use it to see which children are most active and whether the incentive system is working."

